	<div class="post" id="post-17769">
		<div class="post-header">
			<h2><a href="http://www.shescribes.com/2011/08/refreshing-summer-time-drinks-from-taste-of-home.html">Refreshing Summer Time Drinks from Taste of Home</a></h2>
		</div>
		<div class="post-body">
			<div class="socialize-in-content" style="float:left;"><div class="socialize-in-button socialize-in-button-left"><a href="http://twitter.com/share" class="twitter-share-button" data-url="http://www.shescribes.com/2011/08/refreshing-summer-time-drinks-from-taste-of-home.html" data-text="Refreshing Summer Time Drinks from Taste of Home" data-count="vertical" data-via="She_Scribes" ><!--Tweetter--></a></div><div class="socialize-in-button socialize-in-button-left"><iframe src="http://www.facebook.com/plugins/like.php?href=http://www.shescribes.com/2011/08/refreshing-summer-time-drinks-from-taste-of-home.html&amp;layout=box_count&amp;show_faces=true&amp;width=&amp;action=like&amp;font=verdana&amp;colorscheme=light&amp;height=65" scrolling="no" frameborder="0" style="border:none; overflow:hidden; width:px !important; height:65px;" allowTransparency="true"></iframe></div><div class="socialize-in-button socialize-in-button-left"><script src="http://www.stumbleupon.com/hostedbadge.php?s=5&r=http://www.shescribes.com/2011/08/refreshing-summer-time-drinks-from-taste-of-home.html"></script></div></div><p><a href="http://www.shescribes.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/19079150034e29361f0145c.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-17771" title="19079150034e29361f0145c" src="http://www.shescribes.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/19079150034e29361f0145c-219x300.jpg" alt="" width="219" height="300" /></a></p>
<p>Our good friends over at Taste of Home (<a href="http://www.tasteofhome.com/">www.TasteofHome.com</a>) were kind enough to share these delicious summer time recipes. These recipes are going to be featured in their August/September issue of the Taste of Home magazine. They also sent me some mouth-watering recipes that will be ideal for tail gating parties. I&#8217;ll be sharing those in the near future. Until then enjoy these refreshing drinks that are ideal for those lazy summer days.</p>
<p> <a href="http://www.shescribes.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/Summertime-Tea.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-17770" title="RMS#99346" src="http://www.shescribes.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/Summertime-Tea-214x300.jpg" alt="" width="214" height="300" /></a></p>
<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Summertime Tea</strong></span></span></p>
<p><em>Ingredients:</em></p>
<p>- 14 cups water, divided</p>
<p>- 6 individual black tea bags</p>
<p>- 1 ½ cups sugar</p>
<p>- ¾ cup thawed frozen orange juice concentrate</p>
<p>- ¾ cup thawed frozen lemonade concentrate</p>
<p>- 1 cup tequila, optional</p>
<p>- Fresh mint leaves and lemon or lime slices, optional</p>
<p><em>Directions: </em></p>
<p>1. In a large saucepan, bring 4 cups water to a boil. Remove from heat; add tea bags. Cover and steep for 3-5 mins. Discard tea bags.</p>
<p>2. Stir in the sugar, concentrates and remaining water. Add tequila if desired. Refrigerate until chilled. Garnish with mint and lemon.</p>
<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration: underline;"><strong><a href="http://www.shescribes.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/Blueberry-Thirst-Quencher.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-17772" title="RMS#85486" src="http://www.shescribes.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/Blueberry-Thirst-Quencher-200x300.jpg" alt="" width="200" height="300" /></a></strong></span></span></p>
<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Blueberry Thirst Quencher</strong></span></span></p>
<p><em><span style="color: #000000;">Ingredients:</span></em></p>
<p>- 6 cups blueberry juice cocktail, chilled</p>
<p>- 3 cups lemon-lime soda, chilled</p>
<p>- 9 oz blueberry flavored vodka, chilled</p>
<p>- Crushed ice</p>
<p>- 1 cup fresh blueberries</p>
<p>- Sliced peeled mango, optional</p>
<p><em> Directions:</em></p>
<p>1. In a large pitcher, combine the juice, soda, and vodka. Serve over ice; garnish with blueberries and mango.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.shescribes.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/1353766_deck_chairs1.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-17773" title="1353766_deck_chairs" src="http://www.shescribes.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/1353766_deck_chairs1.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="200" /></a></p>
<p>Kimberly</p>
<p><em>*I was not compensated in any way for this post. I posted this, with persmission, for the enjoyment of my site readers. Any opinions expressed are my own. </em></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
